        {
          "username": "Adam M",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "104094626023846271895",
          "user_review_count": 301,
          "user_photo_count": 1153,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX4dC1fQRXH0q4nVU2thdacnTBSYemtCIIyAGU30TPGXReU_yHDA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Cannot say enough positive things about Meds Pharmacy.  I was almost hesitant to leave a review as I didn\u2019t want to have others knowing about them.\n\nAll things aside from their customer service via phone, online and in person to getting prescriptions filled and ability to speak with front desk or pharmacy - it is the only pharmacy where I have not once left or hung up still confused, frustrated or annoyed.\n\nEveryone is extremely friendly knowledgeable, transparent and organized. They will quickly connect you with correct person if they are not appropriate party to speak with. Everything is seamless and it honestly seems too good to be true. As I hope they\u2019ll be able to stick to this high quality service as they grow.\n\nWhen you call - there is never a hold time and if there is it\u2019s a matter of seconds.\n\nThe store itself is easily located near my gym and is clean, relaxed and never a wait time. If so they have comfortable seating and seltzer or flat water for you to enjoy while waiting (max 5 minutes tops).\n\nYou can choose to have delivery or pick up depending on convenience to proximity of where you live.\n\nThe pharmacists understand various situations that are out of everyone\u2019s control in terms of supply and demand. And personally work with you doing everything they can to fulfill your order.\n\nWhile not family owned you get a family owned vibe or relationship from every level of staff who works there.\n\nEd and Mark are extremely friendly, work with you and will explain what\u2019s going on with something, extremely transparent and friendly at the same time.\n\nNo one is trying to push you out the door or provide short confusing answers to your questions. Let alone look miserable working for the larger pharmacies as I\u2019ve experienced at the two dominant pharmacies/stores that are on every block where volume not customer relationship is their priority and business model.\n\nHighly highly recommend. A definite hidden gem.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNodXBQTWVnEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x73f4f995c6d87563!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIChupPMeg%7C%7C?hl=en",
